  "text": "High day-3 FSH and low E 2 suggest DOR. Although the AFC is operator dependant, it is one of the markers of the ovarian reserve. Serum AMH appears to be more reliable than FSH and AFC. The AMH is gonadotropins independent and its assay can be done at any time of the menstrual cycle. The AMH levels below 1 ng/ml are associated with DOR [CITATION_1] .",
